 As a risk-averse undergraduate student who values security and certainty, I would choose a strategy that provides stable earnings over the 75 rounds of the game. Given the payoff structure, it seems beneficial to alternate between R and B each round, since this way we can ensure a regular income (12$ per round) while also having the potential to maximize our earnings in some rounds (45$ if both pick R, or 42$ if both pick B).

So, considering my preferences, I would choose the letter 'R' on an odd numbered round and the letter 'B' on an even numbered round. This strategy allows me to avoid taking unnecessary risks while still having opportunities for potential higher earnings. Here is my choice for the first round: R.

